  "abstract": "In this study, 7561 radiological reports of ankle X-ray images were automatically classified as describing an ankle fracture or not using a large language model. Using a dataset of 250 reports, the language model showed a classification accuracy of 92%. The generated labels were used to train an image classifier to detect ankle fractures on X-ray images. 15,896 images were used for training. The resulting model achieved an accuracy of 89.5% on a test dataset.",
